title: 'Will keep buying'
body: I have started to write with my left hand. And I was trying to find a top wiro bound that is suggested for lefties. But I was unable to find any other brand in an affordable range.  But I found this one. And the paper quality is good. I am attaching the backside of the paper sheet writing with energel and zebra highlighters. There's mostly shadowing. Works for me. I also loved the paper quality of some other products of Navneet too.  It's easy to write on both the sides.  Plus the covers are also nice. Although there room for improvement.  Even the lines are all grey which I like better than black.  Given the quality of the paper and top wiro binding it's value for money if you compare it with other brands.  But I also feel that they should also come out with a cheaper version as well. Which could be used roughly.  I will keep buying these once I have finished. Love these notebooks.
